OL,3,CWoman who took own life told friend of
OL,4,Chusband's alleged abuse, jury told
OL,6,FWhen Mrs Clarke asked whether Trybus
OL,7,Fhad hurt her, Ms Baird replied: "Yes
OL,8,FLibby, I'm afraid he has."
OL,10,FMs Baird described herself as a "total
OL,11,Fmess" and alleged that Trybus had
OL,12,Ffirst attacked her a few months
OL,13,Fpreviously, leading to multiple
OL,14,Fhospital visits.
OL,16,FShe added: "He checks on me a lot now
OL,17,Fand I have to account for any time I'm
OL,18,Fnot at home."
OL,26,@oD@aOUpD@ZO]rD@aOUsD@EO]xD@LOUzD@MO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/11
