OL,3,CWoman who took own life told friend of
OL,4,Chusband's alleged abuse, jury told
OL,6,FGiving evidence, Mrs Clarke told
OL,7,Fjurors that Ms Baird had showed her
OL,8,Fbruises on her eye and abdomen, and
OL,9,Fimages on her phone of bruises.
OL,11,FIn messages from February 2017, Ms
OL,12,FBaird cancelled a meeting with Mrs
OL,13,FClarke, telling her "just feeling
OL,14,Freally sore today from earlier in the
OL,15,Fweek", adding that her doctor had
OL,16,Fconfirmed she had concussion.
OL,18,FShe added: "Still feel groggy and
OL,19,Fspaced out."
OL,26,@uD@UOUwD@EO]zD@LOU{D@LO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/11
