OL,3,CWoman who took own life told friend of
OL,4,Chusband's alleged abuse, jury told
OL,6,FShe added: "He got upset and it made
OL,7,Fit worse. He thinks I'm hiding things
OL,8,Ffrom him."
OL,10,FMrs Clarke wrote: "How could you hide
OL,11,Fwhat he is doing to you?"
OL,13,FMs Baird replied: "I know. I am
OL,14,Fdrained and defeated."
OL,16,FIn May 2017, Ms Baird asked Mrs Clarke
OL,17,Fto contact Women's Aid and ask whether
OL,18,Fthey had a space for her. Ms Baird
OL,19,Flater told her friend she had been
OL,20,Fplanning to leave home at 5pm but
OL,21,F"broke down" and could not.
